WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:26.040 --> 00:00:27.520
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

3
00:00:43.680 --> 00:00:45.960
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

4
00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:48.960
(BABY CRYING)

5
00:00:59.240 --> 00:01:01.520
WOMAN 1: Is it a girl?
WOMAN 2: Yes.

6
00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:03.040
WOMAN 1: Show me its arm.

7
00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:06.840
WOMAN 2: She bears the mark.
WOMAN 3: No! (SOBBING)

8
00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:08.720
(BABY CRYING)

9
00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:12.880
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

10
00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:17.160
(SOBBING) Please. help me!
WOMAN: I can't.

11
00:01:17.280 --> 00:01:19.280
They're going to kill her.

12
00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:21.120
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

13
00:01:24.040 --> 00:01:26.640
Please! Please!

14
00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:29.160
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

15
00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:32.120
Oh. thank you. Ethna.
Thank you.

16
00:01:40.600 --> 00:01:43.120
GUARD: Stand aside
for Queen Bavmorda!

17
00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:54.800
(DOGS BARKING AND SNARLING)

18
00:02:08.280 --> 00:02:10.080
You cannot stop
the prophecy!

19
00:02:10.160 --> 00:02:13.560
This child will have no power
over me. Start the ritual.

20
00:02:13.680 --> 00:02:18.080
No. No!
Where's the baby?

21
00:02:18.160 --> 00:02:20.760
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

22
00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:24.240
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

23
00:02:24.560 --> 00:02:26.400
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

24
00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:28.360
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

25
00:02:28.480 --> 00:02:30.360
GUARD: Silence. wench.
My baby will finish you!

26
00:02:30.480 --> 00:02:32.200
Kill her.

27
00:03:37.920 --> 00:03:40.000
(DOGS BARKING. HOWLING)

28
00:03:47.200 --> 00:03:48.720
(BARKS. HOWLS CONTINUE)

29
00:03:49.280 --> 00:03:50.720
(GASPING. PANTING)

30
00:04:15.120 --> 00:04:17.600
(DOG BELLOWING)

31
00:04:18.680 --> 00:04:20.800
(BABY CRYING)

32
00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:32.400
(BARKING CONTINUES)

33
00:05:28.320 --> 00:05:29.320
(COOING)

34
00:05:42.600 --> 00:05:44.320
(BIRD TWITTERING)

35
00:05:49.480 --> 00:05:50.520
(COOS)

36
00:05:59.480 --> 00:06:01.240
Dada! Dada!

37
00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:07.240
Dada! Dada!
Whoa! Whoa!

38
00:06:09.240 --> 00:06:12.480
Dada! Dada!
We found something
in the river.

39
00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.560
I can't run off
and play with you now.
Ranon.

40
00:06:14.640 --> 00:06:17.520
I've got work to do.
You gotta come. Hurry!

41
00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:19.200
(CHUCKLES)

42
00:06:22.520 --> 00:06:24.240
Come on.

43
00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:29.920
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

44
00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:32.880
But. Dada. it's a baby.

45
00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:37.760
It's not like us.
No. It's not a Nelwyn.

46
00:06:37.880 --> 00:06:42.120
It looks like a Daikini baby.
What's a Daikini?

47
00:06:42.240 --> 00:06:43.840
Daikinis are big.

48
00:06:43.960 --> 00:06:45.920
Giants who live far away.

49
00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:47.280
(LAUGHING)

50
00:06:47.360 --> 00:06:49.760
Oh. she's so cute.

51
00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:52.960
Can't we keep it. Dada?
No!

52
00:06:54.360 --> 00:06:58.720
We'll push it downstream
and forget we ever saw it.
Come on.

53
00:06:58.800 --> 00:07:01.440
MAN: Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

54
00:07:01.560 --> 00:07:04.800
Shh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

55
00:07:05.400 --> 00:07:08.120
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

56
00:07:10.160 --> 00:07:14.640
Mr. Burglekutt.
my husband hasn't
stolen anything!

57
00:07:14.840 --> 00:07:16.160
(GROWLS)

58
00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:23.320
Ufgood.
you still haven't paid
your debts to me.

59
00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:25.320
Where did you get
these seeds?

60
00:07:25.400 --> 00:07:28.200
Well. maybe I used magic.

61
00:07:28.400 --> 00:07:32.320
(LAUGHS) You're no sorcerer.
Ufgood. You're a clown.

62
00:07:32.400 --> 00:07:35.960
I sell the planting seeds
around here. Now tell me
where you got them.

63
00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:39.080
My family's
been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

64
00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:41.920
There's no law against that.
Mr. Burglekutt.

65
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:43.880
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)
Willow. you didn't
leave them alone

66
00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:45.280
by the river?

67
00:07:47.960 --> 00:07:49.600
Magic? You'll need magic

68
00:07:49.680 --> 00:07:53.000
if you expect
to get your planting done
before the rains start.

69
00:07:54.520 --> 00:07:56.200
I will have this land. Ufgood.

70
00:07:56.320 --> 00:07:59.160
And you're gonna end up
working in the mines.

71
00:08:03.520 --> 00:08:05.840
(BURGLEKUTT GRUNTS)
(HOG SNORTING)

72
00:08:10.600 --> 00:08:12.080
(GIGGLING)
Oh. you're lovely.

73
00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:14.520
Yes. you are.
(COOS)

74
00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:16.000
Kiaya!

75
00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:18.440
Oh. Willow!

76
00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:19.720
Good girl. Good girl.

77
00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:23.120
Absolutely.
Under no condition whatsoever

78
00:08:23.200 --> 00:08:26.240
is anyone in this family
to fall in love
with that baby.

79
00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:30.840
Yes. you are.
Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

80
00:08:30.920 --> 00:08:32.920
There we are. Come on.

81
00:08:33.040 --> 00:08:35.520
Hey. I will not be ignored!

82
00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:38.880
Mims? Ranon?

83
00:08:40.480 --> 00:08:41.720
(EXHALES)

84
00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:53.520
(FUSSING)
MIMS: You're gonna be
all clean.

85
00:08:56.080 --> 00:08:58.200
(BABY GIGGLING)

86
00:09:00.200 --> 00:09:02.760
Willow. do you think
we should take her
to the village council?

87
00:09:02.840 --> 00:09:05.440
No. No. They'll think
it's a bad omen.

88
00:09:05.560 --> 00:09:08.400
There'll be a flood
or a drought. and everyone
will blame me for it.

89
00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:11.000
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?"

90
00:09:11.080 --> 00:09:12.840
"That's right.
And he's that
lousy farmer. too.

91
00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:14.320
"Let's get him!"

92
00:09:14.440 --> 00:09:18.600
Willow. calm down.
Calm down?

93
00:09:18.680 --> 00:09:20.680
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

94
00:09:20.760 --> 00:09:24.520
Love. the High Aldwin
hasn't picked
a new apprentice in years.

95
00:09:24.600 --> 00:09:28.200
Tomorrow's gonna
be different. I just know
he's gonna pick me.

96
00:09:28.280 --> 00:09:29.760
(CRYING)

97
00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:34.080
Here. Hold her.
Hey. no.
I don't want her. Kiaya.

98
00:09:34.160 --> 00:09:37.160
Hold her
while I get some milk.
Oh. no. no. Oh.

99
00:09:37.440 --> 00:09:40.640
(GIGGLING)
(SQUEALS)

100
00:09:45.040 --> 00:09:47.040
Dada. she likes you.

101
00:09:47.120 --> 00:09:48.400
(GIGGLES)

102
00:09:50.960 --> 00:09:53.960
(COOING. LAUGHING)

103
00:09:56.920 --> 00:09:58.160
(ROOSTER CROWING)
Bye.

104
00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:02.080
Come on. kids. Let's go.

105
00:10:02.160 --> 00:10:03.440
(MIMS GIGGLING)

106
00:10:07.360 --> 00:10:09.080
(FESTIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

107
00:10:09.160 --> 00:10:13.160
WILLOW: I will now
magically join the rings!

108
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:16.480
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

109
00:10:35.560 --> 00:10:37.920
Whoa!
(LAUGHING)

110
00:10:42.520 --> 00:10:43.960
Thank you. son.

111
00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:48.680
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

112
00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:52.000
(GASPS)
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

113
00:10:54.160 --> 00:10:55.760
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

114
00:11:03.360 --> 00:11:04.960
(HONKING)

115
00:11:05.200 --> 00:11:07.960
Give me a ripe one. Good.

116
00:11:13.880 --> 00:11:18.040
(PIG SQUEALS)
And now.
for my final amazing feat.

117
00:11:18.120 --> 00:11:23.280
I will make
this entire pig disappear!
(SKEPTICAL GROANS)

118
00:11:27.360 --> 00:11:29.360
(SQUEALING)

119
00:11:31.200 --> 00:11:32.680
Mims. see?

120
00:11:33.240 --> 00:11:36.280
Please. watch very closely.

121
00:11:36.400 --> 00:11:38.080
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

122
00:11:40.560 --> 00:11:42.160
(SURPRISED LAUGHTER)

123
00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:47.600
Well...
What happened to your pig?

124
00:11:47.760 --> 00:11:49.440
(PIG SQUEALING)
(GASPS)

125
00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:52.840
(IN ENGLISH)
No! Hey. come here. you!

126
00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:54.640
(CROWD LAUGHING)

127
00:11:57.080 --> 00:12:00.440
I've seen enough. (LAUGHING)

128
00:12:02.440 --> 00:12:04.040
(FANFARE PLAYING)

129
00:12:10.720 --> 00:12:12.880
(LOW. DEEP HORN BLOWS)
(VILLAGERS CHATTERING)

130
00:12:15.400 --> 00:12:17.320
Attention!

131
00:12:17.720 --> 00:12:20.200
The High Aldwin
will now make his choice

132
00:12:20.280 --> 00:12:22.040
for his new apprentice!
You'll be all right.
You'll be fine.

133
00:12:22.120 --> 00:12:25.200
Bring forth
the hopefuls.

134
00:12:25.280 --> 00:12:27.600
Good luck.
Good luck. Dada.

135
00:12:28.200 --> 00:12:31.440
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

136
00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:33.880
Is this a joke? (GUFFAWS)

137
00:12:33.960 --> 00:12:36.080
MAN: Willow?
(BURGLEKUTT CONTINUES
LAUGHING)

138
00:12:42.120 --> 00:12:46.160
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

139
00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:48.800
Forget all you know.

140
00:12:49.280 --> 00:12:51.480
or think you know.

141
00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:55.600
All that you require
is your intuition.

142
00:12:55.680 --> 00:12:59.440
Now. the power
to control the world

143
00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:02.280
is in which finger?

144
00:13:46.880 --> 00:13:49.200
No apprentice this year!
(ONLOOKERS GROAN)

145
00:13:50.680 --> 00:13:53.160
(FESTIVE MUSIC RESUMES)

146
00:14:03.400 --> 00:14:05.040
(CREATURE BELLOWING)

147
00:14:05.600 --> 00:14:08.520
(PANICKED SCREAMS)
(GROWLING)

148
00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:14.080
Where's Mims?
I don't know.
She was right here!

149
00:14:14.560 --> 00:14:16.560
Take Ranon in there. quick!

150
00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:19.240
(GROWLING)

151
00:14:21.400 --> 00:14:22.960
(CRYING)

152
00:14:25.560 --> 00:14:27.160
Mims.

153
00:14:27.240 --> 00:14:28.600
(SNARLING)

154
00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:31.840
Mims!
(ALL SCREAMING)

155
00:14:31.920 --> 00:14:34.080
(CRYING)

156
00:14:34.200 --> 00:14:35.240
(SNARLING)

157
00:14:38.080 --> 00:14:39.920
(GASPS)
(CRYING)

158
00:14:40.040 --> 00:14:41.640
Mims!

159
00:14:46.360 --> 00:14:47.920
I'm scared. Dada!

160
00:14:48.040 --> 00:14:49.200
(BABY CRYING)

161
00:14:55.720 --> 00:14:58.360
(FEROCIOUS GROWLING)

162
00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:00.960
Come on!

163
00:15:06.800 --> 00:15:08.440
(DOG SNARLING)

164
00:15:12.760 --> 00:15:13.960
(YELLING)

165
00:15:19.400 --> 00:15:21.120
Vohnkar!

166
00:15:21.360 --> 00:15:22.400
(GROWLS)

167
00:15:23.120 --> 00:15:25.640
(DOG WHIMPERS)
(MEN GRUNTING)

168
00:15:32.320 --> 00:15:33.920
MAN 1: Check to make sure
it's not still alive.

169
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.400
MAN 2: It's dead!

170
00:15:37.640 --> 00:15:39.480
Dada! Dada!

171
00:15:42.640 --> 00:15:45.160
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

172
00:15:45.280 --> 00:15:47.000
(BABY CRYING)

173
00:15:48.480 --> 00:15:49.880
Mommy.

174
00:15:50.960 --> 00:15:52.280
Kiaya!

175
00:15:59.840 --> 00:16:02.840
Kiaya! Kiaya!

176
00:16:03.640 --> 00:16:05.360
I'm here.
(BABY COOS)

177
00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:07.360
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

178
00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:11.680
Oh. Kiaya.

179
00:16:11.760 --> 00:16:13.040
(BABY FUSSING)

180
00:16:13.200 --> 00:16:15.760
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

181
00:16:15.840 --> 00:16:18.680
We have to take her
to the village council.

182
00:16:22.760 --> 00:16:24.600
(VILLAGERS CLAMORING)

183
00:16:31.760 --> 00:16:33.360
Silence!

184
00:16:33.480 --> 00:16:37.080
One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

185
00:16:37.200 --> 00:16:39.240
And you can be assured
that they won't give up

186
00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:41.160
until they find
what they're looking for!

187
00:16:41.240 --> 00:16:44.560
MAN 1: It's a sign!
MAN 2:
Who's to blame for this?

188
00:16:44.640 --> 00:16:47.360
MAN 3:
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

189
00:16:47.560 --> 00:16:48.720
(ALL SHOUTING IN AGREEMENT)

190
00:16:48.800 --> 00:16:52.240
VILLAGERS: (CHANTING)
Yes! In the pit!
In the pit! In the pit!

191
00:16:52.400 --> 00:16:54.640
In the pit! In the pit!

192
00:16:54.720 --> 00:16:57.040
In the pit! In the pit!

193
00:16:57.200 --> 00:17:00.520
Willow. Willow Ufgood.
(CHANTING STOPS)

194
00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:05.200
Come forward.

195
00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:07.240
(VILLAGERS MURMURING)

196
00:17:09.640 --> 00:17:10.640
(CHICKEN CLUCKS)

197
00:17:11.520 --> 00:17:15.520
WILLOW: My children
found this baby alone
by the river. High Aldwin.

198
00:17:17.480 --> 00:17:18.920
(CRYING)

199
00:17:21.400 --> 00:17:23.520
A Daikini child.
(VILLAGERS GASPING)

200
00:17:23.600 --> 00:17:26.520
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

201
00:17:26.600 --> 00:17:28.040
VILLAGERS: Yeah!

202
00:17:28.120 --> 00:17:31.840
They'll kill her! You can't!
It isn't one of us.

203
00:17:31.920 --> 00:17:34.520
This child is special!

204
00:17:35.320 --> 00:17:38.880
This child must be taken
beyond the boundaries
of our village.

205
00:17:38.960 --> 00:17:44.000
All the way across
the great river
to the Daikini crossroads.

206
00:17:44.120 --> 00:17:46.000
Well. who'll do that?

207
00:17:47.160 --> 00:17:52.080
It seems only fair
that the man to take this baby
to the crossroads

208
00:17:52.160 --> 00:17:55.560
be the very man
who plucked it
out of the river.

209
00:17:56.320 --> 00:17:59.320
I nominate Willow Ufgood.
(VILLAGERS SHOUT IN AGREEMENT)

210
00:17:59.600 --> 00:18:00.920
No!

211
00:18:01.960 --> 00:18:04.640
I will consult the bones!

212
00:18:13.600 --> 00:18:16.920
The bones tell me nothing.

213
00:18:17.960 --> 00:18:19.880
(BABY COOS)

214
00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:24.160
Do you have any love
for this child?

215
00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:34.320
Yes.

216
00:18:36.360 --> 00:18:37.440
Yes. I do.

217
00:18:37.520 --> 00:18:39.760
The bones have spoken!

218
00:18:39.840 --> 00:18:41.440
(VILLAGERS MURMURING)

219
00:18:41.600 --> 00:18:44.160
Willow Ufgood.
the safety of this village

220
00:18:44.280 --> 00:18:45.840
depends upon you.

221
00:18:45.920 --> 00:18:49.960
Praise the bones!
VILLAGERS: Praise the bones!

222
00:18:50.200 --> 00:18:52.280
HIGH ALDWIN:
But you will need help.

223
00:18:52.400 --> 00:18:57.120
Who has the courage
to protect our brave fellow
on his journey?

224
00:19:00.160 --> 00:19:01.760
I'll go with him.

225
00:19:02.360 --> 00:19:05.800
Ah. Meegosh.
Excellent choice.

226
00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:07.160
I'll go!

227
00:19:07.240 --> 00:19:09.240
VILLAGERS: (SHOUTING)
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

228
00:19:09.360 --> 00:19:13.120
No! Not Vohnkar!
He's the best warrior
in the village!

229
00:19:13.200 --> 00:19:16.160
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

230
00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:26.720
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

231
00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:30.200
And according to the bones.

232
00:19:30.560 --> 00:19:35.000
that leader is you.
Burglekutt!

233
00:19:36.720 --> 00:19:38.880
Vohnkar!

234
00:19:39.360 --> 00:19:43.400
What's your problem. son?
How do you mean?

235
00:19:44.160 --> 00:19:48.800
When I held up my fingers.
what was your first impulse?

236
00:19:48.880 --> 00:19:51.920
Well. it was stupid.
Just tell me.

237
00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:55.400
To pick my own finger.
A-ha!

238
00:19:56.040 --> 00:19:57.880
That was the correct answer.

239
00:19:58.040 --> 00:20:02.080
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone
in the village.

240
00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:05.600
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

241
00:20:05.720 --> 00:20:10.000
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

242
00:20:11.440 --> 00:20:13.080
These will protect you.

243
00:20:14.240 --> 00:20:17.360
Acorns?
They're magic!

244
00:20:17.440 --> 00:20:19.080
Anything you throw them at

245
00:20:19.160 --> 00:20:20.880
turns to stone.

246
00:20:24.160 --> 00:20:26.600
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

247
00:20:40.440 --> 00:20:42.600
MIMS: Are you scared. Dada?

248
00:20:43.440 --> 00:20:44.760
No!

249
00:20:45.080 --> 00:20:46.560
Even with fairies in the woods

250
00:20:46.640 --> 00:20:48.960
that'll put you to sleep
for a hundred years?

251
00:20:50.800 --> 00:20:52.840
Doesn't bother me.
Brownies?

252
00:20:52.960 --> 00:20:56.280
Dragons?
Trolls?

253
00:20:56.400 --> 00:20:59.840
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

254
00:20:59.960 --> 00:21:03.560
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

255
00:21:03.640 --> 00:21:06.160
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

256
00:21:06.240 --> 00:21:08.440
Me. too.
Me. too. Dada.

257
00:21:09.520 --> 00:21:12.240
What a lucky father I am.

258
00:21:12.320 --> 00:21:14.640
I wish I could take
you bobbins with me.

259
00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:19.400
Goodbye. Dada.

260
00:21:23.160 --> 00:21:25.120
Go play! Go on.

261
00:21:30.480 --> 00:21:32.680
We've never been apart.

262
00:21:36.080 --> 00:21:38.160
I miss you already.

263
00:21:39.520 --> 00:21:43.480
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

264
00:21:43.560 --> 00:21:45.520
I'll be back
before you know it.

265
00:21:47.520 --> 00:21:50.360
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

266
00:21:52.200 --> 00:21:54.840
And here.

267
00:21:57.480 --> 00:21:59.840
This will bring you luck.

268
00:22:13.720 --> 00:22:15.600
Good brave people!

269
00:22:17.920 --> 00:22:20.520
The outer world
is no place for a Nelwyn.

270
00:22:20.600 --> 00:22:24.760
Give the baby
to the first Daikini you see.
then hurry home.

271
00:22:28.320 --> 00:22:30.040
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

272
00:22:32.880 --> 00:22:35.520
HIGH ALDWIN: (IN ENGLISH)
Go in the direction
the bird is flying!

273
00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:42.400
It's going back
to the village!

274
00:22:44.240 --> 00:22:46.880
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

275
00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:48.320
Move out!

276
00:23:09.760 --> 00:23:11.280
(FUSSING)

277
00:23:12.960 --> 00:23:15.280
Hold on. Meegosh.
What's wrong?

278
00:23:16.400 --> 00:23:17.760
We have to stop.

279
00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:20.520
Stop? Why?

280
00:23:20.600 --> 00:23:22.760
The baby's sick.
(BAWLING)

281
00:23:27.160 --> 00:23:29.840
She's not sick!
Let me see.

282
00:23:32.440 --> 00:23:33.600
(RETCHES)

283
00:23:34.160 --> 00:23:35.520
Take her! Take her!

284
00:23:35.640 --> 00:23:37.280
(LAUGHING)
(BURGLEKUTT GROANING)

285
00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:40.120
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

286
00:23:40.480 --> 00:23:41.960
(COOING)

287
00:23:42.760 --> 00:23:44.160
(GROANING) Clean me up.

288
00:23:48.600 --> 00:23:51.560
BAVMORDA: I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

289
00:23:51.640 --> 00:23:55.000
Sorsha. you're useless!
I'm backtracking
the nursemaid's trail.

290
00:23:55.120 --> 00:23:56.800
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

291
00:23:59.840 --> 00:24:01.840
Ah. General Kael. at last.

292
00:24:02.720 --> 00:24:06.320
KAEL: My queen.
I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

293
00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:10.720
Well done.
But now I have
another task for you.

294
00:24:10.840 --> 00:24:15.600
Help my daughter
to find that tiny.
helpless baby

295
00:24:15.680 --> 00:24:18.280
that continues somehow
to elude her.

296
00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:21.600
The baby of the prophecy?

297
00:24:21.680 --> 00:24:25.040
The one
that would destroy you?
I need that baby alive.

298
00:24:25.160 --> 00:24:27.160
I must perform the ritual

299
00:24:27.280 --> 00:24:31.040
that will exile
the child's spirit
into oblivion.

300
00:24:31.200 --> 00:24:34.080
Find her!
I don't need his help. Mother.

301
00:24:34.160 --> 00:24:36.200
You'll do as I say. child.

302
00:24:42.840 --> 00:24:44.520
SEER: I read the signs.

303
00:24:44.600 --> 00:24:47.640
One day. I fear.
your daughter will betray you.

304
00:24:48.480 --> 00:24:51.880
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

305
00:24:57.520 --> 00:24:59.320
(BABY COOING)

306
00:25:02.840 --> 00:25:03.800
(BABY SQUEALING)

307
00:25:03.880 --> 00:25:05.320
(DOGS BARKING)
(MEN SHOUTING)

308
00:25:08.520 --> 00:25:09.840
Move!

309
00:25:11.280 --> 00:25:12.680
Into the bush.
Come on. Move!

310
00:25:14.520 --> 00:25:16.040
(HORSE WHINNIES)

311
00:25:17.640 --> 00:25:18.640
Come on!

312
00:25:18.920 --> 00:25:20.640
(DOGS SNARLING)

313
00:25:31.080 --> 00:25:32.960
MAN 1:
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

314
00:25:33.080 --> 00:25:35.200
But a group of them
are on the road somewhere.

315
00:25:35.280 --> 00:25:37.840
MAN 2: They couldn't
have gone far!

316
00:25:37.920 --> 00:25:39.920
MAN 1: Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

317
00:25:42.240 --> 00:25:43.600
(BARKING FADES)

318
00:25:43.680 --> 00:25:45.200
(SPUTTERING SIGH)

319
00:25:47.760 --> 00:25:50.040
Come. We'll keep
to the woods.

320
00:26:29.960 --> 00:26:31.800
That's it!

321
00:26:31.920 --> 00:26:33.440
It's the crossroads!

322
00:26:36.240 --> 00:26:39.960
(DOGS HOWLING IN DISTANCE)

323
00:26:51.360 --> 00:26:54.280
VOHNKAR: Keep this fire high.
We don't know
what's out there.

324
00:26:54.360 --> 00:26:56.440
(WHIMPERS)

325
00:26:58.920 --> 00:27:00.520
(CREATURE SCREECHING)

326
00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:02.080
What was that?

327
00:27:03.960 --> 00:27:05.280
Get the spears!

328
00:27:08.360 --> 00:27:09.560
(CRYING)

329
00:27:17.480 --> 00:27:19.000
(SCREECHING)
(GASPS)

330
00:27:21.640 --> 00:27:23.480
(GROWLING)
(GRUNTING)

331
00:27:24.360 --> 00:27:30.040
Give me some water. peck.
or you die. Do you understand?

332
00:27:31.040 --> 00:27:32.360
Water.
Yeah.

333
00:27:32.880 --> 00:27:34.360
(GRUNTS. GROANS)

334
00:27:35.400 --> 00:27:36.640
Hurry up!

335
00:27:41.200 --> 00:27:43.680
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

336
00:27:45.200 --> 00:27:47.520
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

337
00:27:48.320 --> 00:27:49.400
We can't give her
to him!

338
00:27:49.560 --> 00:27:51.520
Somebody put him there
for a reason.

339
00:27:51.600 --> 00:27:53.440
Ufgood. we've got
to get rid of her.

340
00:27:53.560 --> 00:27:55.680
Those soldiers
are after us.
Shh.

341
00:27:56.560 --> 00:27:58.240
He's looking
right at us.

342
00:28:03.560 --> 00:28:05.800
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

343
00:28:05.880 --> 00:28:07.240
I'm somebody.

344
00:28:08.840 --> 00:28:12.560
Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby.
(SMOOCHING SOUNDS)

345
00:28:14.880 --> 00:28:19.000
I trust him completely.
But he tried to strangle me.

346
00:28:19.440 --> 00:28:22.840
I want to go home!
No. Burglekutt!

347
00:28:22.920 --> 00:28:27.080
We should wait!
Are you challenging
my authority?

348
00:28:27.160 --> 00:28:30.200
As far as this baby
is concerned. yes.

349
00:28:30.280 --> 00:28:32.280
Don't listen to him.
Burglekutt.

350
00:28:34.000 --> 00:28:38.160
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

351
00:28:39.600 --> 00:28:42.760
That's a bad idea. Very bad.
Dangerous out there.

352
00:28:42.880 --> 00:28:44.640
VOHNKAR: Get the gear. men.

353
00:28:44.760 --> 00:28:47.680
Vohnkar.
It's not his decision!

354
00:28:47.760 --> 00:28:49.200
Burglekutt.

355
00:28:50.280 --> 00:28:51.680
you're troll dung.

356
00:28:51.760 --> 00:28:53.440
Don't let him talk to you
that way. Burglekutt.

357
00:28:53.560 --> 00:28:55.240
Listen here. runt.

358
00:28:55.320 --> 00:28:59.280
While you're wasting
your time here. your fields
aren't getting planted.

359
00:28:59.960 --> 00:29:01.280
Think about it!

360
00:29:01.360 --> 00:29:04.040
Burglekutt. I'm gonna...

361
00:29:04.120 --> 00:29:05.800
You're gonna what?

362
00:29:07.840 --> 00:29:09.800
(LAUGHS)

363
00:29:11.120 --> 00:29:13.760
Someday. Burglekutt. Someday.

364
00:29:14.120 --> 00:29:15.800
Vohnkar. let's go!

365
00:29:19.480 --> 00:29:21.480
Meegosh. are you coming?

366
00:29:24.400 --> 00:29:25.400
I'm staying.

367
00:29:25.760 --> 00:29:28.160
(LAUGHS) Come on. men.

368
00:29:28.640 --> 00:29:32.320
Burglekutt. let me out
of here. I'll take care
of the baby. I swear.

369
00:29:33.280 --> 00:29:35.240
Just let me out of here.
Please!

370
00:29:35.320 --> 00:29:39.160
Vohnkar. let me borrow
that spear just for a minute.

371
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:41.160
Well. at least get me
some water!

372
00:29:41.240 --> 00:29:44.120
Burglekutt.
don't leave me alone
with these two!

373
00:29:44.440 --> 00:29:46.160
(FRUSTRATED GRUNT)

374
00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:48.320
(BABY CRYING)

375
00:29:48.440 --> 00:29:50.800
What'll we do now. Willow?

376
00:29:51.680 --> 00:29:53.440
Well. that was
really stupid. peck.

377
00:29:53.840 --> 00:29:55.240
Don't call me a peck.

378
00:29:55.520 --> 00:29:58.120
Oh. I'm sorry. peck.

379
00:29:58.400 --> 00:30:01.520
Peck. peck. peck. peck.
You be careful!

380
00:30:03.280 --> 00:30:06.120
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

381
00:30:07.440 --> 00:30:09.880
I'll throw it at you
and turn you to stone.

382
00:30:10.720 --> 00:30:12.120
Whoo.

383
00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:14.200
I'm really scared.

384
00:30:14.320 --> 00:30:16.840
No. don't! Don't!

385
00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:20.360
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

386
00:30:21.280 --> 00:30:22.560
Oh. I wouldn't want
to waste it.

387
00:30:23.160 --> 00:30:28.520
Ha! Peck. peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck. peck. peck. peck!

388
00:30:29.120 --> 00:30:30.680
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

389
00:30:54.560 --> 00:30:56.160
(WHINNIES)

390
00:30:56.240 --> 00:30:57.560
(BOTH GASPING)

391
00:30:58.560 --> 00:30:59.920
MEEGOSH: What was that?

392
00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:05.560
Morning. boys.

393
00:31:07.960 --> 00:31:09.400
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

394
00:31:11.600 --> 00:31:13.920
I don't think
I introduced myself yesterday.

395
00:31:15.040 --> 00:31:18.560
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh...

396
00:31:19.040 --> 00:31:21.240
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

397
00:31:21.360 --> 00:31:23.080
He's dangerous.

398
00:31:23.160 --> 00:31:24.320
I am not.

399
00:31:24.560 --> 00:31:25.920
(HORSE WHINNIES)

400
00:31:26.440 --> 00:31:27.760
Good.

401
00:31:32.040 --> 00:31:33.240
Stop! Wait!

402
00:31:36.200 --> 00:31:38.120
(HORSE WHINNIES)
Whoa!

403
00:31:39.440 --> 00:31:40.600
(SCOFFS)

404
00:31:45.080 --> 00:31:46.360
What's going on?

405
00:31:46.440 --> 00:31:47.760
Smells like a battle.

406
00:31:49.360 --> 00:31:51.280
I suppose you're a warrior.

407
00:31:51.680 --> 00:31:53.920
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

408
00:31:54.560 --> 00:31:55.840
(WILLOW SCOFFS)

409
00:31:56.960 --> 00:31:58.280
Say. uh...

410
00:31:59.600 --> 00:32:00.640
Could I have
some of that water?

411
00:32:02.800 --> 00:32:04.400
(SIPS NOISILY)

412
00:32:06.400 --> 00:32:07.800
(SOBBING)

413
00:32:10.400 --> 00:32:12.160
I don't know why I try.

414
00:32:12.760 --> 00:32:15.120
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

415
00:32:20.480 --> 00:32:23.000
I guess
I am gonna die here.
Who cares?

416
00:32:23.120 --> 00:32:26.000
Here.
Thanks. friend. Oh!

417
00:32:26.120 --> 00:32:28.160
(DISTANT RUMBLING)
What's that?

418
00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:31.760
MADMARTIGAN: I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

419
00:32:31.840 --> 00:32:35.440
five or six wagons
and about a thousand fools.

420
00:32:36.160 --> 00:32:37.960
(MADMARTIGAN GRUNTING)

421
00:32:39.680 --> 00:32:41.800
Thank you. Oh...
Come on. Meegosh.

422
00:32:42.320 --> 00:32:44.120
(PANTING)

423
00:32:47.680 --> 00:32:50.040
WILLOW:
It's gonna be all right.
little bobbin.

424
00:32:50.480 --> 00:32:52.840
(DRUMS BEATING)

425
00:32:57.320 --> 00:32:58.440
(FUSSING)

426
00:32:58.520 --> 00:33:00.120
Everything's gonna
be all right.

427
00:33:00.200 --> 00:33:02.080
(DRUMBEATS CONTINUE)

428
00:33:03.920 --> 00:33:06.600
Excuse me. sir.
Out of the way. peck!

429
00:33:09.360 --> 00:33:10.920
WILLOW: Uh. pardon me.

430
00:33:11.240 --> 00:33:12.520
Uh...

431
00:33:13.200 --> 00:33:15.920
(DRUMBEATS CONTINUE)

432
00:33:19.040 --> 00:33:20.480
Excuse me. sir.

433
00:33:21.920 --> 00:33:24.560
We found one of your babies
in our village.

434
00:33:24.680 --> 00:33:26.320
Will you please
take care of her?

435
00:33:27.880 --> 00:33:29.960
We're going into battle.
little ones.

436
00:33:30.040 --> 00:33:32.120
Find a woman
to take care of her.

437
00:33:32.240 --> 00:33:34.880
They thought
you were a woman. Airk.

438
00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:38.200
Well... (LAUGHS)

439
00:33:38.280 --> 00:33:41.200
Madmartigan!
What did you do this time?

440
00:33:41.480 --> 00:33:43.280
Nothing you wouldn't
have done in my place.

441
00:33:43.400 --> 00:33:45.280
AIRK: I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

442
00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:47.200
Well. at least
I'm not down there
herding sheep.

443
00:33:47.280 --> 00:33:49.080
What are you doing
this far north?

444
00:33:49.200 --> 00:33:51.920
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

445
00:33:52.920 --> 00:33:54.080
The castle?

446
00:33:54.200 --> 00:33:56.080
Bavmorda's troops
are crushing everything
in sight.

447
00:33:56.200 --> 00:33:58.480
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

448
00:33:58.560 --> 00:34:00.400
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

449
00:34:00.480 --> 00:34:04.600
Madmartigan.
I still serve Galladoorn.

450
00:34:05.440 --> 00:34:07.920
You serve no one. Remember?

451
00:34:08.960 --> 00:34:11.280
Sit in your coffin and rot.

452
00:34:12.920 --> 00:34:15.080
MADMARTIGAN:
Wait. Airk. You need me!
(HORSE WHINNIES)

453
00:34:15.840 --> 00:34:18.240
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

454
00:34:18.840 --> 00:34:20.880
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off

455
00:34:20.960 --> 00:34:22.880
and stick it on a pig pole!

456
00:34:40.560 --> 00:34:42.320
(BABY FUSSING)

457
00:34:42.440 --> 00:34:44.960
I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

458
00:34:49.480 --> 00:34:51.440
We're running out of food.

459
00:34:54.480 --> 00:34:56.640
Nobody's gonna take care
of that baby.

460
00:34:56.760 --> 00:34:58.360
You know why?

461
00:34:58.480 --> 00:34:59.800
Nobody cares.

462
00:35:02.960 --> 00:35:04.480
Except me.

463
00:35:05.640 --> 00:35:07.800
You want to go back
to your families.

464
00:35:07.920 --> 00:35:09.720
I want out of this cage.

465
00:35:10.600 --> 00:35:14.280
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her
like she was my own.

466
00:35:15.200 --> 00:35:17.120
I believe he would. Willow.

467
00:35:17.840 --> 00:35:19.960
He doesn't know anything
about babies.

468
00:35:20.800 --> 00:35:25.200
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

469
00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:28.320
If I had somebody in my life.

470
00:35:29.520 --> 00:35:31.160
a little daughter. perhaps.

471
00:35:32.680 --> 00:35:35.200
I might have a reason
to go on living.

472
00:35:39.200 --> 00:35:42.000
You can't leave me
in here to die.

473
00:35:42.080 --> 00:35:44.560
Not when all I want to do
is protect her.

474
00:35:51.680 --> 00:35:54.360
(SCREAMS. LAUGHS)

475
00:35:57.960 --> 00:36:01.320
I feel better! (LAUGHS)

476
00:36:01.800 --> 00:36:03.720
You've done the right thing!

477
00:36:03.800 --> 00:36:05.880
Okay. All right. All right.
Whoo!

478
00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:10.400
You gotta promise to feed her.
Come to Daddy. little darling.

479
00:36:10.560 --> 00:36:13.360
And keep her clean.
Absolutely.

480
00:36:16.320 --> 00:36:17.560
(MADMARTIGAN
AND BABY GIGGLING)

481
00:36:18.160 --> 00:36:20.240
Whee!
(BABY SQUEALS)

482
00:36:24.040 --> 00:36:25.400
She likes me.

483
00:36:26.440 --> 00:36:28.000
(GIGGLES)

484
00:36:28.440 --> 00:36:30.440
Here are her changing rags.

485
00:36:30.560 --> 00:36:32.600
And her milk bladder.
Any milk in there?

486
00:36:32.720 --> 00:36:34.520
It's for her!

487
00:36:34.600 --> 00:36:36.720
I wouldn't steal from a baby.

488
00:36:39.920 --> 00:36:41.920
You worry too much. peck.

489
00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:43.600
It's Willow.

490
00:36:43.760 --> 00:36:45.080
I mean Willow.

491
00:36:46.440 --> 00:36:51.040
Now listen. boys.
Willow. you've done
the right thing.

492
00:36:52.200 --> 00:36:55.080
Now I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

493
00:37:01.440 --> 00:37:03.600
Goodbye. little one.

494
00:37:15.200 --> 00:37:17.120
Please take good care of her.

495
00:37:19.440 --> 00:37:21.440
I give you my word of honor!

496
00:37:28.800 --> 00:37:32.120
WILLOW: Meegosh. slow down!
Oh. come on!

497
00:37:32.200 --> 00:37:36.400
If we hurry. we can be home
by tomorrow morning.
We'll be heroes.

498
00:37:37.800 --> 00:37:39.960
Do you really think so?
Sure.

499
00:37:40.080 --> 00:37:42.320
"Look. there's Willow
and Meegosh.

500
00:37:42.440 --> 00:37:45.400
"The heroes have come home."

501
00:37:45.480 --> 00:37:47.840
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

502
00:37:47.960 --> 00:37:49.680
Yeah. Medals.

503
00:37:49.800 --> 00:37:51.440
(BOTH LAUGHING)

504
00:37:52.960 --> 00:37:54.400
Meegosh.

505
00:37:58.240 --> 00:38:00.640
Did we do the right thing?

506
00:38:00.800 --> 00:38:02.000
Absolutely.

507
00:38:02.080 --> 00:38:03.640
There's nothing
to worry about.

508
00:38:07.320 --> 00:38:08.880
(BABY CRYING)

509
00:38:09.680 --> 00:38:12.000
MAN: Hyah! Ha-ha!

510
00:38:12.400 --> 00:38:16.080
I stole a baby!
I stole a baby!

511
00:38:16.160 --> 00:38:18.800
(LAUGHS) Hyah!

512
00:38:19.560 --> 00:38:21.280
That's my baby!
(BABY CRYING)

513
00:38:21.360 --> 00:38:22.880
Stop! Wait! Come back!

514
00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:25.880
MAN: Left. you stupid bird.
Left! (LAUGHS)

515
00:38:27.480 --> 00:38:29.120
(ARROW TWANGS)

516
00:38:30.000 --> 00:38:31.520
(GRUNTS)
Ow!

517
00:38:32.840 --> 00:38:34.800
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

518
00:38:36.480 --> 00:38:39.520
Come on. Meegosh! Ow!
(BROWNIES LAUGHING)

519
00:38:41.200 --> 00:38:44.320
(BOTH GRUNTING)

520
00:38:45.520 --> 00:38:46.920
WILLOW: We'll outrun 'em!

521
00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:50.560
(BOTH YELLING)
(BROWNIES LAUGHING)

522
00:38:52.120 --> 00:38:55.040
Hey. ugly. wake up!
(LAUGHING)

523
00:38:57.280 --> 00:38:58.480
WILLOW: Huh?

524
00:38:59.720 --> 00:39:01.280
(GRUNTS. GROANS)

525
00:39:02.120 --> 00:39:04.480
Stand your ground.
He's our prisoner.
Where am I?

526
00:39:04.560 --> 00:39:06.720
Meegosh. where's the baby?

527
00:39:07.560 --> 00:39:08.920
CHERLINDREA:
Bring the Nelwyns to me.

528
00:39:09.040 --> 00:39:10.160
All right. you heard her!

529
00:39:10.240 --> 00:39:14.080
What's going on?
Shut up.
or I'll break your nose.

530
00:39:14.160 --> 00:39:16.560
You are mine to toy with.

531
00:39:17.760 --> 00:39:19.160
Forward!

532
00:39:21.560 --> 00:39:23.200
Get the rope.
(ALL GRUNTING)

533
00:39:23.360 --> 00:39:24.360
Come on.

534
00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:27.080
Where...

535
00:39:27.200 --> 00:39:30.560
Where did you get that baby?

536
00:39:30.880 --> 00:39:35.400
I stole it
from a stupid Daikini.
(LAUGHS)

537
00:39:36.800 --> 00:39:38.920
CHERLINDREA:
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

538
00:39:39.440 --> 00:39:41.960
And stop pestering them.
Uh-oh.

539
00:39:43.240 --> 00:39:44.760
(MUTTERING)

540
00:39:47.440 --> 00:39:48.520
(ROPE POPS)

541
00:39:48.600 --> 00:39:49.640
(SHOUTS)

542
00:39:53.600 --> 00:39:56.440
(SHOUTING. LAUGHING)

543
00:39:58.520 --> 00:40:00.200
CHERLINDREA:
Welcome to my kingdom.

544
00:40:03.280 --> 00:40:04.280
(KISSES)

545
00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:11.200
I'm so happy to meet you.
Willow Ufgood.

546
00:40:11.280 --> 00:40:12.840
WILLOW: How do you know
my name?

547
00:40:13.600 --> 00:40:15.280
Elora Danan told me.

548
00:40:16.000 --> 00:40:19.440
Elora? Elora. Willow is here.

549
00:40:23.280 --> 00:40:24.640
But she's just a baby.

550
00:40:25.240 --> 00:40:27.400
She's very special.

551
00:40:28.120 --> 00:40:31.840
My Brownies have been
searching for her ever since
we heard she was born.

552
00:40:34.200 --> 00:40:37.480
Elora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

553
00:40:38.800 --> 00:40:40.000
Me?

554
00:40:40.160 --> 00:40:43.120
Yes. She likes you.

555
00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:49.640
And Elora Danan knows
you have the courage
to help us.

556
00:40:49.760 --> 00:40:52.960
Take my wand
to the sorceress Fin Raziel.

557
00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:57.320
She will guide you
and Elora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

558
00:40:57.400 --> 00:41:00.800
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

559
00:41:00.880 --> 00:41:04.520
You need a warrior for a job
like this. I'm a nobody.

560
00:41:04.880 --> 00:41:07.200
Elora. you don't want me.

561
00:41:08.160 --> 00:41:11.840
Tell her. I'm short.
even for a Nelwyn.

562
00:41:15.840 --> 00:41:17.200
Hello?

563
00:41:24.760 --> 00:41:27.840
Elora Danan must survive!

564
00:41:27.920 --> 00:41:29.600
She must fulfill her destiny

565
00:41:29.680 --> 00:41:32.800
and bring about
the downfall
of Queen Bavmorda.

566
00:41:32.880 --> 00:41:36.040
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

567
00:41:36.160 --> 00:41:40.160
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control
the lives

568
00:41:40.240 --> 00:41:44.040
of your village.
your children. everyone.

569
00:41:50.080 --> 00:41:53.200
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

570
00:41:54.280 --> 00:41:56.840
The choice is yours.

571
00:41:58.080 --> 00:42:01.040
(THUNDER CRACKLING)
(WIND WHISTLING)

572
00:42:21.400 --> 00:42:25.080
Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
Huh?

573
00:42:25.920 --> 00:42:29.040
It's time to go home.
Home?

574
00:42:32.840 --> 00:42:36.440
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

575
00:42:37.120 --> 00:42:40.280
And I think of her every day.
Willow...

576
00:42:40.960 --> 00:42:44.000
And tell her I'm not going
to let anything happen
to the baby.

577
00:42:44.440 --> 00:42:46.600
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

578
00:42:48.280 --> 00:42:49.600
I hope so.

579
00:42:51.240 --> 00:42:53.120
Listen. be careful.

580
00:43:00.040 --> 00:43:03.520
I know the way. Franjean.
You always think
you know the way.

581
00:43:03.640 --> 00:43:05.320
I am the leader!

582
00:43:05.440 --> 00:43:07.440
How long will it take
to find this Raziel?

583
00:43:07.520 --> 00:43:08.520
FRANJEAN: Not long.

584
00:43:08.640 --> 00:43:12.040
ROOL: She's been exiled
to an island
just over those hills.

585
00:43:12.160 --> 00:43:14.960
She's what?
Exiled.

586
00:43:15.040 --> 00:43:18.880
By the evil Queen Bavmorda.
(LAUGHS)

587
00:43:18.960 --> 00:43:21.640
Rool. you fool.
He does not need
to know everything.

588
00:43:21.720 --> 00:43:23.800
I didn't tell him everything.
You told him enough.

589
00:43:23.880 --> 00:43:25.440
What did I say?
You mentioned the island.

590
00:43:25.520 --> 00:43:27.520
Wait a minute.
You mentioned the queen.

591
00:43:27.640 --> 00:43:29.080
ROOL: (YELLING) So?

592
00:43:29.160 --> 00:43:32.200
What do you mean?
What are you saying.
mysterious island?

593
00:43:32.320 --> 00:43:34.720
Don't play
with that wand.

594
00:43:35.080 --> 00:43:38.280
Cherlindrea told you.
it holds vast powers.

595
00:43:38.360 --> 00:43:40.240
Only a great sorcerer
can use it.

596
00:43:40.320 --> 00:43:43.280
not a stupid peck like you.
(LAUGHING)

597
00:43:43.680 --> 00:43:46.120
This way.
No. No. No.
I don't think so.

598
00:43:46.200 --> 00:43:48.520
All right. then this way.
Eh. nope.

599
00:43:48.640 --> 00:43:51.120
This way.
This way?

600
00:43:51.200 --> 00:43:53.160
That's what I said.

601
00:43:54.320 --> 00:43:55.280
This way.

602
00:43:55.360 --> 00:43:58.440
You sure you know
where you're going?
Of course.

603
00:43:58.520 --> 00:44:01.320
With us as your guides.
no harm will befall you.

604
00:44:01.840 --> 00:44:03.840
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

605
00:44:12.040 --> 00:44:13.680
(ELORA FUSSING)

606
00:44:14.120 --> 00:44:15.400
MAN: Take it up!

607
00:44:18.200 --> 00:44:20.280
We are not
going in there!

608
00:44:20.360 --> 00:44:22.120
But Elora needs fresh milk.

609
00:44:22.200 --> 00:44:26.880
And we are drenched.
You are not in command.
shorty. I am!

610
00:44:26.960 --> 00:44:29.360
You hear me? Whoa!

611
00:44:33.360 --> 00:44:35.680
(LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING)

612
00:44:38.960 --> 00:44:41.400
(GLASS BREAKING)
(CROWD YELLING)

613
00:44:53.720 --> 00:44:55.280
(MAN LAUGHING)

614
00:45:08.560 --> 00:45:11.000
Excuse me? Excuse me.
(LAUGHING)

615
00:45:11.080 --> 00:45:13.840
Could you spare some milk
for this poor hungry baby?

616
00:45:13.920 --> 00:45:17.840
Get out of here. peck!
Get out of here
or we'll cook ya!

617
00:45:33.120 --> 00:45:35.680
ROOL: Ooh. look at her!

618
00:45:35.760 --> 00:45:38.440
I could use
a love potion on her!

619
00:45:38.560 --> 00:45:41.360
Franjean! Hey!
Give me that dust
of broken heart.

620
00:45:41.440 --> 00:45:43.800
Come on! Give it to me!

621
00:45:43.920 --> 00:45:46.640
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

622
00:45:47.040 --> 00:45:49.120
(GROWLS. SNEEZES)

623
00:45:49.280 --> 00:45:50.840
(YELLS)
(THUMPS)

624
00:45:50.960 --> 00:45:53.440
Hey. quiet! You want
to get us killed?

625
00:45:55.960 --> 00:45:57.120
(SNEEZES)

626
00:45:57.280 --> 00:45:59.440
(GRUNTS)

627
00:46:00.520 --> 00:46:04.120
FRANJEAN: Oh. Rool!
Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

628
00:46:04.960 --> 00:46:06.160
(MEOWING)

629
00:46:06.520 --> 00:46:08.400
(SIGHING DEEPLY)

630
00:46:08.480 --> 00:46:10.920
You are so beautiful!

631
00:46:11.040 --> 00:46:12.400
(MEOWS)

632
00:46:12.480 --> 00:46:15.320
Your eyes! Your whiskers!

633
00:46:15.440 --> 00:46:17.160
I have to kiss you!

634
00:46:17.240 --> 00:46:19.480
Rool! That dust
of broken heart!

635
00:46:19.840 --> 00:46:21.840
(MEOWS)
(ROOL SCREAMS)

636
00:46:24.320 --> 00:46:26.960
(PANTING. GRUNTING)

637
00:46:34.160 --> 00:46:36.560
Beer! (LAUGHS)

638
00:46:39.360 --> 00:46:41.880
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

639
00:46:46.480 --> 00:46:48.520
WOMAN: Hurry! Hurry!

640
00:46:48.640 --> 00:46:49.880
My husband's coming!

641
00:46:50.000 --> 00:46:52.600
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

642
00:46:52.680 --> 00:46:54.200
How do I look?
Cover your face up!

643
00:46:54.320 --> 00:46:55.320
Not you!

644
00:46:56.880 --> 00:46:58.360
Where the hell
did you come from?

645
00:46:58.480 --> 00:47:00.680
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

646
00:47:00.800 --> 00:47:04.520
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby
from you. Daikini.

647
00:47:04.640 --> 00:47:06.720
while you were taking
a pee-pee!
Cover your face!

648
00:47:06.880 --> 00:47:09.480
You are crawling
with Brownies.

649
00:47:09.600 --> 00:47:10.920
(SHRIEKS) I hate Brownies!

650
00:47:11.040 --> 00:47:13.600
(FRANJEAN LAUGHING)
Whoa!

651
00:47:13.720 --> 00:47:15.840
Where is he? Where?
WOMAN: Hello. dear.

652
00:47:15.920 --> 00:47:18.040
There's nobody here
but me and. uh. my. uh...

653
00:47:18.160 --> 00:47:21.280
I'll kill him!
...my cousin. Hilda.

654
00:47:21.360 --> 00:47:23.280
Hilda?
WOMAN: Hilda.

655
00:47:23.400 --> 00:47:26.120
Hilda!
This is my husband. Llug.

656
00:47:26.240 --> 00:47:27.600
(IN WOMAN'S VOICE)
Mmm. Big husband.
WOMAN: Yes.

657
00:47:27.720 --> 00:47:29.920
MADMARTIGAN: How do you do?
(LAUGHING)

658
00:47:30.040 --> 00:47:32.200
LLUG: Hilda! Ooh.

659
00:47:32.400 --> 00:47:35.560
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

660
00:47:35.680 --> 00:47:37.680
Hey! Give her back!

661
00:47:37.760 --> 00:47:40.400
Pecks make
terrible nursemaids.
Nursemaid?

662
00:47:40.480 --> 00:47:42.520
They get too excited.
(GRUNTS)

663
00:47:43.400 --> 00:47:45.680
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

664
00:47:45.920 --> 00:47:49.320
Huh?
Hey. hey. hey. hey!

665
00:47:49.400 --> 00:47:51.600
(LAUGHING LEWDLY)
Stop. please. Ooh.

666
00:47:52.760 --> 00:47:54.560
Come on. Fight like a man!

667
00:47:54.760 --> 00:47:55.760
(GRUNTS)

668
00:47:56.320 --> 00:47:57.720
Want to breed?

669
00:47:58.520 --> 00:48:00.720
Tempting. but no.

670
00:48:01.200 --> 00:48:03.080
(GROWLING)

671
00:48:04.080 --> 00:48:06.000
Thank you.
Time to leave.

672
00:48:06.080 --> 00:48:07.640
Bye. Hilda!
SOLDIER: Take them out.

673
00:48:07.960 --> 00:48:10.960
(ALL GASPING)
Hey! Come along!

674
00:48:11.080 --> 00:48:13.200
MADMARTIGAN:
Careful. you lout!
Move along!

675
00:48:13.280 --> 00:48:15.920
SOLDIER: Gather up
all these babies.

676
00:48:16.080 --> 00:48:18.680
SORSHA: That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

677
00:48:18.760 --> 00:48:20.440
(CROWD CLAMORING)

678
00:48:22.000 --> 00:48:23.600
That's not the one.

679
00:48:28.120 --> 00:48:31.080
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

680
00:48:31.160 --> 00:48:33.760
(IN WOMAN'S VOICE)
Yes. Yes. I am.
Let me see it.

681
00:48:33.840 --> 00:48:35.160
No! Don't let her!

682
00:48:35.440 --> 00:48:36.840
Aah!

683
00:48:37.640 --> 00:48:39.800
I gave you an order. woman!

684
00:48:40.240 --> 00:48:41.720
(GRUNTS)

685
00:48:48.800 --> 00:48:52.480
You're... You're beautiful.

686
00:48:52.960 --> 00:48:55.800
And you're very strong.
Thank you.

687
00:48:58.920 --> 00:49:00.720
You're no woman!

688
00:49:01.480 --> 00:49:03.040
Now. honey. take it easy.
Not a woman?

689
00:49:03.160 --> 00:49:06.080
(IN NORMAL VOICE) Gentlemen...
Not a woman!

690
00:49:06.160 --> 00:49:07.840
Meet Llug.
(GROWLS)

691
00:49:10.160 --> 00:49:12.000
After them!
Out of the way!

692
00:49:18.600 --> 00:49:19.600
To the horses!

693
00:49:30.520 --> 00:49:31.600
Hyah!
(WHINNIES)

694
00:49:31.680 --> 00:49:36.200
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

695
00:49:36.640 --> 00:49:38.520
(GRUNTING. GROANING)

696
00:49:39.680 --> 00:49:40.840
LLUG: He's not a woman!

697
00:49:42.600 --> 00:49:44.520
(HORSE WHINNYING)
(SHOUTS)

698
00:49:44.760 --> 00:49:46.160
SOLDIER:
Don't let them get away!

699
00:49:48.880 --> 00:49:51.200
Madmartigan. stop!

700
00:49:57.000 --> 00:49:59.200
(WHIMPERING)

701
00:49:59.320 --> 00:50:01.720
(GRUNTING. GROANING)

702
00:50:11.280 --> 00:50:13.840
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you...

703
00:50:15.720 --> 00:50:18.480
Ow!
Prepare to die!

704
00:50:20.680 --> 00:50:21.720
Whoa!

705
00:50:22.720 --> 00:50:24.400
(GRUNTS)

706
00:50:30.520 --> 00:50:32.080
(GROANS)

707
00:50:42.080 --> 00:50:44.680
Madmartigan! Stop!

708
00:50:56.400 --> 00:50:57.920
(BOTH GRUNTING)

709
00:51:01.160 --> 00:51:04.240
No more beer.

710
00:51:10.120 --> 00:51:11.440
(GASPS)

711
00:51:12.720 --> 00:51:13.960
(GROANING)

712
00:51:15.280 --> 00:51:16.960
Franjean. help me!

713
00:51:21.800 --> 00:51:23.360
Rool!
Help!

714
00:51:23.440 --> 00:51:25.880
Rool! Rool.

715
00:51:28.160 --> 00:51:31.480
Rool! What are you doing?
Help me!

716
00:51:34.120 --> 00:51:36.720
(GRUNTING)

717
00:51:37.280 --> 00:51:39.040
Come on. I am.
Pull me in.

718
00:51:39.120 --> 00:51:40.760
ROOL: Yeah. pull!

719
00:51:54.200 --> 00:51:56.000
(SQUEALS)

720
00:51:56.120 --> 00:51:57.480
(HORSE WHINNIES)

721
00:52:00.320 --> 00:52:01.840
You can't have her!

722
00:52:08.080 --> 00:52:09.840
Whoa! (GRUNTS)

723
00:52:16.400 --> 00:52:19.960
Rool. this isn't funny!
Help me cut the rope!

724
00:52:20.080 --> 00:52:22.400
(GRUNTING)

725
00:52:32.880 --> 00:52:34.520
Whoa!

726
00:52:36.120 --> 00:52:38.320
(LAUGHING. CHEERING)

727
00:52:57.200 --> 00:52:59.160
MADMARTIGAN:
Willow. stay down!

728
00:53:03.520 --> 00:53:05.280
Whoa!

729
00:53:06.240 --> 00:53:08.000
Whoa!

730
00:53:08.520 --> 00:53:09.880
Have you gone crazy?

731
00:53:10.000 --> 00:53:12.160
WILLOW: You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

732
00:53:12.520 --> 00:53:13.480
We're getting off!

733
00:53:13.560 --> 00:53:15.920
Hyah! Hyah!
(YELLING)

734
00:53:29.080 --> 00:53:30.600
(MEN GROANING)

735
00:53:41.600 --> 00:53:43.480
Whoa! Whoa!

736
00:53:43.640 --> 00:53:45.680
(GRUNTING. GROANING)

737
00:53:45.760 --> 00:53:48.440
Oh. Rool. (GRUNTS)

738
00:53:49.120 --> 00:53:50.760
Now we stop. peck.

739
00:53:52.600 --> 00:53:56.760
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

740
00:53:57.600 --> 00:53:59.120
Madmartigan!

741
00:53:59.240 --> 00:54:02.120
You never. ever drive
that fast with an infant!

742
00:54:03.800 --> 00:54:05.800
I just saved
that infant's life!

743
00:54:07.440 --> 00:54:08.800
(URGING HORSES)

744
00:54:09.480 --> 00:54:11.200
FRANJEAN: Gather your wits.
Come on.

745
00:54:11.280 --> 00:54:14.800
ROOL: Don't worry about me.
I'm fine!
Come on!

746
00:54:15.120 --> 00:54:16.720
(HOOFBEATS APPROACHING)

747
00:54:16.800 --> 00:54:18.720
Get down!

748
00:54:18.800 --> 00:54:20.480
ROOL: Uh. where am I? Oh!

749
00:54:22.480 --> 00:54:24.480
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

750
00:54:24.640 --> 00:54:26.640
(GROANS. GRUNTS)

751
00:54:27.320 --> 00:54:28.840
(DOGS BARKING)

752
00:54:34.760 --> 00:54:36.520
(BARKING CONTINUES)

753
00:54:41.000 --> 00:54:42.080
ROOL: Ah. Franjean!

754
00:54:42.160 --> 00:54:44.000
You better clear out.
Willow.

755
00:54:44.080 --> 00:54:45.240
Before those troops
come back.

756
00:54:45.320 --> 00:54:48.440
ROOL: Ah. my head!
We don't need him. Elora.

757
00:54:49.240 --> 00:54:50.840
(CRYING)

758
00:54:56.640 --> 00:54:58.680
WILLOW: Madmartigan. wait!

759
00:54:58.800 --> 00:55:02.080
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

760
00:55:02.160 --> 00:55:04.560
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

761
00:55:04.680 --> 00:55:07.840
My help? (SCOFFS)
What do you need my help for?

762
00:55:07.960 --> 00:55:09.840
You're a sorcerer!

763
00:55:09.960 --> 00:55:13.280
You're a great warrior
and a swordsman.

764
00:55:13.360 --> 00:55:16.360
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

765
00:55:17.360 --> 00:55:20.200
Are you trying to make
my life more difficult
than it already is?

766
00:55:20.320 --> 00:55:21.680
(DOGS BARKING)
(GASPS)

767
00:55:23.920 --> 00:55:25.280
(BARKING CONTINUES)

768
00:55:25.520 --> 00:55:27.520
Hurry! Big dogs!

769
00:55:28.840 --> 00:55:32.280
Look. I'm sorry I got angry.

770
00:55:32.360 --> 00:55:34.120
We wouldn't have escaped
without you.

771
00:55:36.040 --> 00:55:39.560
(COOING)

772
00:55:48.000 --> 00:55:51.240
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

773
00:55:52.720 --> 00:55:56.320
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

774
00:55:58.240 --> 00:55:59.560
That way.

775
00:56:00.680 --> 00:56:04.400
You are drunk.
and when you are drunk.
you forget that...

776
00:56:04.480 --> 00:56:06.520
I am in charge!
You are in charge.

777
00:56:06.600 --> 00:56:08.480
Fine. Then which way do we go?

778
00:56:09.760 --> 00:56:11.160
That way!
That way!

779
00:56:11.240 --> 00:56:13.600
(CROW CAWING)

780
00:56:13.920 --> 00:56:18.200
Oh. no! That's the way
I'm going.

781
00:56:18.800 --> 00:56:21.240
All right. all right.
You can follow me
as far as the lake.

782
00:56:21.360 --> 00:56:22.640
But that's it!

783
00:56:23.600 --> 00:56:27.360
You're not going south.
are you?
No. just as far as the lake.

784
00:56:27.440 --> 00:56:32.560
Good. Mumbo. Jumbo.
I am hungry. Go get me
some eggs or something.

785
00:56:32.640 --> 00:56:34.640
We are not afraid of you!

786
00:56:34.760 --> 00:56:36.600
Now!
(BOTH SHRIEKING)

787
00:56:38.400 --> 00:56:40.120
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

788
00:56:42.080 --> 00:56:45.240
Kael. have you found
the child?

789
00:56:46.800 --> 00:56:48.440
The search goes on.
my queen.

790
00:56:49.440 --> 00:56:51.440
Why. with my powers.

791
00:56:51.520 --> 00:56:54.360
with the strength
of my great army.

792
00:56:54.440 --> 00:56:58.160
can you not find
one little child?

793
00:56:58.280 --> 00:57:00.880
We look even now.
It won't be long.

794
00:57:00.960 --> 00:57:03.800
Find the child.
Find the child!

795
00:57:04.800 --> 00:57:06.560
Time is running out.

796
00:57:14.960 --> 00:57:17.120
Good night.
She is kind of cute.

797
00:57:18.960 --> 00:57:20.320
When she's quiet.

798
00:57:22.560 --> 00:57:24.400
She's really a princess.

799
00:57:24.480 --> 00:57:27.840
Really? And you're
a great sorcerer.

800
00:57:28.600 --> 00:57:29.960
And I'm the king of Kashmir.

801
00:57:31.040 --> 00:57:32.400
Go to sleep. Willow.

802
00:57:34.120 --> 00:57:35.800
Good night. Madmartigan.

803
00:57:36.840 --> 00:57:39.600
ROOL: Rats! Big rats! Rats!

804
00:57:39.680 --> 00:57:41.840
(GRUNTS) Rats! Rat...

805
00:57:43.280 --> 00:57:46.520
Rool. you and that
stupid rat dream!

806
00:57:56.440 --> 00:57:58.000
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

807
00:58:02.600 --> 00:58:03.840
(SCREAMS)

808
00:58:04.200 --> 00:58:06.520
Huh? Willow?

809
00:58:08.360 --> 00:58:09.680
Willow?

810
00:58:11.520 --> 00:58:12.840
Oh.

811
00:58:13.160 --> 00:58:14.160
(YAWNING) There you are.

812
00:58:14.240 --> 00:58:15.720
Madmartigan!

813
00:58:17.360 --> 00:58:18.880
(YAWNING) Night. Willow.

814
00:58:26.200 --> 00:58:28.480
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

815
00:58:31.480 --> 00:58:33.520
ROOL: This way! This way!

816
00:58:43.520 --> 00:58:45.240
(ELORA COOING)

817
00:58:45.360 --> 00:58:47.080
What are you doing?

818
00:58:47.200 --> 00:58:49.560
I found some black root.
She loves it!

819
00:58:49.680 --> 00:58:52.840
Black root?
I am the father
of two children.

820
00:58:52.920 --> 00:58:55.040
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

821
00:58:55.120 --> 00:58:58.200
Well. my mother raised us
on black root.

822
00:58:58.280 --> 00:59:00.560
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

823
00:59:00.680 --> 00:59:03.400
Doesn't it. Sticks?
Her name is not Sticks.

824
00:59:03.560 --> 00:59:06.520
She's Elora Danan.
the future empress
of Tir Asleen.

825
00:59:06.600 --> 00:59:09.200
And the last thing
she's gonna want
is a hairy chest!

826
00:59:10.040 --> 00:59:11.560
(ELORA WHIMPERING)

827
00:59:13.280 --> 00:59:15.040
MADMARTIGAN:
Did you see what he did?

828
00:59:15.120 --> 00:59:16.600
He stole our black root.

829
00:59:16.720 --> 00:59:18.560
I'll get some more.
Don't worry about it.

830
00:59:22.920 --> 00:59:26.720
There it is! The island!
(BOTH LAUGHING)

831
00:59:29.520 --> 00:59:30.880
We made it.

832
00:59:32.240 --> 00:59:35.600
FRANJEAN: We have led you
to the island
of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

833
00:59:35.680 --> 00:59:39.280
We'll get a boat
in that village.
A big boat. (CHUCKLES)

834
00:59:57.640 --> 00:59:59.960
Well. looks like
I got you here.

835
01:00:00.040 --> 01:00:02.240
You! What did you do?

836
01:00:02.320 --> 01:00:05.480
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

837
01:00:06.000 --> 01:00:08.080
I found a boat.
We're all set.

838
01:00:08.160 --> 01:00:11.720
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

839
01:00:11.840 --> 01:00:14.160
Lizards! Who are you
calling lizards?

840
01:00:14.360 --> 01:00:16.960
(GROWLING. YAPPING)

841
01:00:17.120 --> 01:00:19.280
ROOL:
Your mother was a lizard!

842
01:00:22.800 --> 01:00:25.200
MADMARTIGAN: Goodbye. Sticks.
(FUSSING)

843
01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:30.680
If you really are a princess.

844
01:00:30.800 --> 01:00:32.120
take care of him.

845
01:00:38.160 --> 01:00:39.920
(ELORA CRYING)

846
01:00:40.680 --> 01:00:42.920
Madmartigan!
What?

847
01:00:44.360 --> 01:00:45.400
Thanks.

848
01:00:55.760 --> 01:00:57.520
Hey! Aah!
(SPITTING)

849
01:00:57.960 --> 01:01:00.640
ROOL: Keep walking. hero!
Don't even turn around!

850
01:01:02.040 --> 01:01:04.880
(CRIES)
It's all right. Elora.

851
01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:07.120
(THUNDER RUMBLING)
Go to sleep.

852
01:01:07.200 --> 01:01:11.640
Nobody'll find you here.
I'll be back with Fin Raziel
very soon.

853
01:01:11.720 --> 01:01:14.720
We will guard her
with our meager lives.

854
01:01:14.880 --> 01:01:16.040
(DISTANT THUNDER CONTINUES)

855
01:01:43.280 --> 01:01:44.640
Raziel!

856
01:01:46.080 --> 01:01:49.720
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk
to you. please!

857
01:01:53.760 --> 01:01:55.360
Raziel!

858
01:02:01.640 --> 01:02:03.080
She's not here.

859
01:02:08.600 --> 01:02:10.000
(SCREECHING)
Aah!

860
01:02:10.120 --> 01:02:13.920
(HIGH. SQUEAKY VOICE)
Get back! Who are you?

861
01:02:15.040 --> 01:02:17.280
Who are you?

862
01:02:20.040 --> 01:02:21.040
I'm Willow Ufgood.

863
01:02:21.120 --> 01:02:23.120
What are you doing here?

864
01:02:23.240 --> 01:02:26.880
I've come to find
the great sorceress.
Fin Raziel.

865
01:02:26.960 --> 01:02:29.480
That's me! I'm Raziel!

866
01:02:31.960 --> 01:02:33.520
This can't be right!

867
01:02:33.640 --> 01:02:37.120
One of Bavmorda's spells
transformed me.

868
01:02:39.440 --> 01:02:41.800
Believe me.
it could have been worse!

869
01:02:43.400 --> 01:02:47.840
Well. this wand is for you.
It's from Cherlindrea.

870
01:02:48.520 --> 01:02:52.320
Then the prophecy is true.
The princess has been born.

871
01:02:52.640 --> 01:02:54.000
Take me to her.

872
01:02:57.760 --> 01:02:59.840
It is Elora Danan.

873
01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:02.440
Isn't she beautiful?
(CHUCKLING)

874
01:03:02.640 --> 01:03:05.480
Isn't she beautiful?

875
01:03:06.160 --> 01:03:09.000
That's Raziel?
I don't know.

876
01:03:09.120 --> 01:03:11.920
I expected
something more grand.
Less. uh...

877
01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:13.720
Fuzzy.
Fuzzy!

878
01:03:13.840 --> 01:03:18.320
You must use the wand.
Turn me back
into my human form.

879
01:03:18.400 --> 01:03:21.160
What do I do?
You mean
you're not a sorcerer?

880
01:03:22.320 --> 01:03:24.920
Yes. Sorta.

881
01:03:25.000 --> 01:03:27.080
I'm a farmer.
(BOTH SIGHING IN DISGUST)

882
01:03:27.680 --> 01:03:29.440
But I do know a few tricks.

883
01:03:29.640 --> 01:03:33.720
Tricks? Cherlindrea sent you?
You must learn real magic.

884
01:03:36.040 --> 01:03:37.000
(HORSE WHINNYING)

885
01:03:37.080 --> 01:03:38.360
Horses!
Horses!

886
01:03:38.880 --> 01:03:42.680
RAZIEL: Quick! Take her!
Hurry! Hurry!
(GASPS)

887
01:03:50.760 --> 01:03:53.440
FRANJEAN: I knew
he was a traitor!

888
01:03:55.600 --> 01:03:57.280
Sorry about this. peck.

889
01:03:57.360 --> 01:03:59.280
Keep your mouth shut!
(GROANS)

890
01:03:59.600 --> 01:04:02.480
Told you we'd find him
without your help.

891
01:04:02.560 --> 01:04:04.480
Give me that baby.
No!

892
01:04:04.560 --> 01:04:07.040
(ELORA CRYING)

893
01:04:07.880 --> 01:04:09.240
Give her back!

894
01:04:09.840 --> 01:04:11.880
(SHRIEKS) Leave me alone!
Don't touch me!

895
01:04:12.080 --> 01:04:13.400
(HORSE WHINNIES)

896
01:04:18.160 --> 01:04:19.680
This is the one
we're looking for.

897
01:04:19.760 --> 01:04:22.560
We must take it
back to Nockmaar.
(CHITTERING)

898
01:04:26.080 --> 01:04:27.920
Lose your skirt?

899
01:04:36.160 --> 01:04:37.560
I've still got what counts.

900
01:04:37.640 --> 01:04:39.320
Not for long.

901
01:04:40.720 --> 01:04:41.760
(GROANS)

902
01:04:45.600 --> 01:04:48.600
Bring him.
Over here!

903
01:04:49.440 --> 01:04:51.280
(GRUNTING)

904
01:05:03.240 --> 01:05:05.960
(PANTING. GRUNTING)

905
01:05:07.240 --> 01:05:09.440
We'll never keep up
with those horses.

906
01:05:10.240 --> 01:05:13.520
Then we will have
to track them.
That would take forever.

907
01:05:13.600 --> 01:05:16.120
Besides. even if we find them.
they'll catch us.

908
01:05:16.240 --> 01:05:19.440
stick us in cages.
torture us
and finally devour us.

909
01:05:19.560 --> 01:05:21.560
Are you suggesting
we go home?

910
01:05:21.640 --> 01:05:23.160
No. This is more fun!

911
01:05:23.280 --> 01:05:24.400
All right.

912
01:05:24.480 --> 01:05:26.160
Fine. then. Come on!

913
01:05:28.800 --> 01:05:31.280
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

914
01:05:32.960 --> 01:05:36.320
(HORSE WHINNIES)
(ELORA CRYING)

915
01:05:40.200 --> 01:05:43.640
I'm worried about Elora.
She doesn't sound good.

916
01:05:43.720 --> 01:05:46.320
Hurry! Practice the chant
I taught you!

917
01:05:47.480 --> 01:05:49.120
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

918
01:05:50.880 --> 01:05:52.400
(IN ENGLISH)
I can't remember
the middle part.

919
01:05:52.480 --> 01:05:54.200
Locktwaar!

920
01:05:54.320 --> 01:05:57.160
That's the word
that pleads for change.

921
01:05:58.120 --> 01:05:59.520
Locktwaar.

922
01:06:03.440 --> 01:06:06.600
Elora's cold and hungry.
She knows me.

923
01:06:06.680 --> 01:06:08.440
Please. let me
take care of her.

924
01:06:08.520 --> 01:06:10.600
I don't need help from a peck.

925
01:06:10.680 --> 01:06:12.240
(CRYING CONTINUES)

926
01:06:12.360 --> 01:06:14.360
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

927
01:06:15.120 --> 01:06:16.680
What are you staring at?

928
01:06:17.520 --> 01:06:18.840
Your leg.

929
01:06:19.840 --> 01:06:20.800
I'd like to break it.

930
01:06:20.880 --> 01:06:23.600
You may find
that difficult. slave.

931
01:06:23.680 --> 01:06:25.600
while I'm up here
and you're down there.

932
01:06:28.800 --> 01:06:30.200
I hate that woman.

933
01:06:52.240 --> 01:06:53.800
(GROANING)

934
01:07:03.800 --> 01:07:05.200
SORSHA: Hyah!

935
01:07:09.840 --> 01:07:11.120
I found it. Kael.

936
01:07:11.240 --> 01:07:13.560
(ELORA CRYING)

937
01:07:14.360 --> 01:07:16.080
That should make
my mother happy.

938
01:07:17.360 --> 01:07:18.720
What are they gonna do to her?

939
01:07:24.400 --> 01:07:26.080
(DOGS HOWLING)

940
01:07:27.560 --> 01:07:31.000
(PANTING. GROWLING)

941
01:07:31.080 --> 01:07:32.760
(WILLOW CHANTING
IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

942
01:07:40.240 --> 01:07:43.600
(SNIFFING) That's magic?
Smells terrible.

943
01:07:43.680 --> 01:07:46.560
It's the life spark.
It forms after...
Well. it stinks!

944
01:07:46.880 --> 01:07:50.120
This whole thing stinks!
Ignore him. Willow.

945
01:07:50.240 --> 01:07:54.080
He's a fool!
If only I had
a sword! (GRUNTS)

946
01:07:54.320 --> 01:07:56.320
If only you'd quit
talking about it.

947
01:07:56.720 --> 01:07:59.600
Willow. you must transform me
to my human self.

948
01:08:00.480 --> 01:08:02.240
But. Raziel.
I'm not ready yet.

949
01:08:02.960 --> 01:08:05.240
You'd better be. Get me down.

950
01:08:06.480 --> 01:08:09.480
(GRUNTS)
(SQUEALS)

951
01:08:09.800 --> 01:08:12.080
Ow! (GROANS)

952
01:08:14.640 --> 01:08:17.440
Why don't you help me
get out of here instead of
chattering with that muskrat?

953
01:08:17.880 --> 01:08:21.400
Muskrat! When I change back
to my former self.

954
01:08:21.480 --> 01:08:23.480
I will crush this army.

955
01:08:23.880 --> 01:08:27.280
and take Elora Danan
to Tir Asleen.

956
01:08:27.360 --> 01:08:29.920
where she will be safe.

957
01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:32.000
(CHOMPING)
Ow!

958
01:08:32.640 --> 01:08:34.080
What'd you bite me for?

959
01:08:34.520 --> 01:08:37.640
You need three drops
of your blood
to put in the potion.

960
01:08:38.080 --> 01:08:39.360
Well. you could've warned me.

961
01:08:40.080 --> 01:08:41.160
(SCOFFS)

962
01:08:41.440 --> 01:08:43.480
For beginners.
there's some pain.

963
01:08:43.960 --> 01:08:48.760
but don't let anything
break your concentration.

964
01:08:53.760 --> 01:08:55.160
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

965
01:08:56.840 --> 01:09:00.600
Hello. everybody!
We have arrived!
You are saved.

966
01:09:00.680 --> 01:09:03.240
BOTH: Shh!
RAZIEL: Don't interrupt.

967
01:09:05.040 --> 01:09:06.360
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

968
01:09:09.400 --> 01:09:11.040
What are you gonna look like
if this works?

969
01:09:11.160 --> 01:09:13.440
Don't interrupt.
Sorry.

970
01:09:13.520 --> 01:09:15.600
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

971
01:09:15.680 --> 01:09:18.880
I am a young. beautiful woman.

972
01:09:19.680 --> 01:09:21.040
Concentrate. Willow.

973
01:09:21.120 --> 01:09:22.720
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

974
01:09:24.680 --> 01:09:27.720
RAZIEL: No! You're losing me!

975
01:09:27.800 --> 01:09:28.960
(STRETCHING SOUND)

976
01:09:29.040 --> 01:09:30.560
(CONTINUES CHANTING)

977
01:09:31.560 --> 01:09:33.240
(RAZIEL WHIMPERING)

978
01:09:36.520 --> 01:09:39.160
(GROANS)
You all right?
Nice try. Willow.

979
01:09:39.280 --> 01:09:40.880
(BIRD CAWING)

980
01:09:47.040 --> 01:09:52.200
RAZIEL: Farmers!
Cherlindrea sends me farmers!

981
01:09:52.520 --> 01:09:54.520
The Nelwyn
really butchered that one.

982
01:09:55.280 --> 01:09:56.720
I'm sorry. Raziel.

983
01:09:57.200 --> 01:10:00.240
You want out?
Easy. We can pick a lock.
Come on.

984
01:10:01.560 --> 01:10:02.840
No. No. no. Like this!

985
01:10:02.920 --> 01:10:05.240
I know what I'm doing.
It's my spear. Leave it alone.

986
01:10:05.920 --> 01:10:07.240
Let me do it.

987
01:10:07.920 --> 01:10:09.240
Out of the way. rodents.

988
01:10:10.920 --> 01:10:12.240
FRANJEAN:
Take your hand off that.

989
01:10:12.360 --> 01:10:16.480
You leave that alone.
you stupid. fat Daikini!

990
01:10:16.600 --> 01:10:17.920
Ow!

991
01:10:18.480 --> 01:10:20.720
(LAUGHING)
Dust of broken hearts.

992
01:10:22.000 --> 01:10:23.280
(GRUNTS)

993
01:10:27.040 --> 01:10:28.520
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

994
01:10:28.600 --> 01:10:30.880
(BOTH GRUNTING)

995
01:10:31.920 --> 01:10:34.080
Ha. ha! There. You are free!

996
01:10:34.960 --> 01:10:37.760
Come on. Madmartigan.
Let's get Elora Danan
out of here.

997
01:10:38.800 --> 01:10:42.440
Yeah. It'll be fun.
Come on!

998
01:10:55.040 --> 01:10:56.640
Are you all right?
Yeah.

999
01:10:58.600 --> 01:11:00.640
I feel good.

1000
01:11:00.920 --> 01:11:03.640
The dust of broken hearts.
Uh...

1001
01:11:04.680 --> 01:11:06.040
Come on!

1002
01:11:12.800 --> 01:11:15.280
ROOL: Let me see!
You always see.
FRANJEAN: Let me see.

1003
01:11:15.640 --> 01:11:18.000
There's Elora. right there.
on those furs.

1004
01:11:18.160 --> 01:11:20.320
(FUSSING)

1005
01:11:20.480 --> 01:11:22.440
FRANJEAN: Hey. wait!
Leave this to us.

1006
01:11:22.520 --> 01:11:23.960
It's too dangerous for you.

1007
01:11:24.320 --> 01:11:25.400
Only one of us
should go in there.

1008
01:11:25.480 --> 01:11:28.000
I've had experience
in this sort of thing.
I know what I'm doing.

1009
01:11:56.520 --> 01:11:58.040
BOTH: Uh-oh.

1010
01:11:59.320 --> 01:12:01.640
(WHISPERING)
Wait. Shh! No! No!

1011
01:12:13.040 --> 01:12:14.360
I love you.

1012
01:12:14.560 --> 01:12:15.880
WILLOW: Madmartigan!

1013
01:12:16.160 --> 01:12:17.360
What are you doing?

1014
01:12:17.440 --> 01:12:19.560
Take the baby and go!
Come on! Come on!

1015
01:12:30.840 --> 01:12:33.160
Oh. Sorsha.
(GROANS)

1016
01:12:33.240 --> 01:12:34.760
(BOTH GROANING)

1017
01:12:35.880 --> 01:12:37.760
Wake from this hateful sleep.

1018
01:12:38.720 --> 01:12:40.400
It deprives me of your beauty.

1019
01:12:41.720 --> 01:12:45.160
The beauty of your eyes...
One move. jackass.

1020
01:12:45.240 --> 01:12:46.720
and you really
will be a woman.

1021
01:12:48.200 --> 01:12:51.520
You are my sun! My moon!

1022
01:12:52.080 --> 01:12:53.720
My starlit sky.

1023
01:12:54.080 --> 01:12:56.400
Without you.
I dwell in darkness.

1024
01:12:57.520 --> 01:12:58.800
I love you.

1025
01:12:59.360 --> 01:13:00.720
What are you doing here?

1026
01:13:01.160 --> 01:13:03.800
Your power has enchanted me.
I stand helpless against it.

1027
01:13:04.920 --> 01:13:06.240
Come to me. now.

1028
01:13:06.400 --> 01:13:08.760
Tonight. let me worship you
in my arms.

1029
01:13:08.880 --> 01:13:10.240
Get away from me!

1030
01:13:10.560 --> 01:13:11.880
I love you!

1031
01:13:12.200 --> 01:13:13.600
Stop saying that!

1032
01:13:14.240 --> 01:13:16.560
How can I stop
the beating of my heart?

1033
01:13:16.640 --> 01:13:18.440
It pounds like never before.

1034
01:13:18.560 --> 01:13:21.000
Out of fear.
Out of love!

1035
01:13:21.120 --> 01:13:23.400
I can stop it. I'll kill you.

1036
01:13:24.120 --> 01:13:25.960
Death. next to love.
is a trivial thing.

1037
01:13:29.600 --> 01:13:31.960
Your touch is worth
100.000 deaths.

1038
01:13:37.080 --> 01:13:39.400
What goes on here?
(ELORA CRYING)

1039
01:13:44.160 --> 01:13:45.560
Deceiver!

1040
01:13:47.080 --> 01:13:48.440
KAEL: Stop him!

1041
01:13:49.080 --> 01:13:50.440
(MAN GROANS)

1042
01:13:58.480 --> 01:13:59.800
KAEL: Captain. get up!

1043
01:14:03.320 --> 01:14:05.440
(ALL YELLING)

1044
01:14:11.440 --> 01:14:13.000
You are great.

1045
01:14:13.960 --> 01:14:15.680
(CHUCKLES. GRUNTS)

1046
01:14:16.760 --> 01:14:18.040
Get on that shield!

1047
01:14:18.160 --> 01:14:19.440
(GRUNTS)

1048
01:14:29.960 --> 01:14:31.320
Sorsha!

1049
01:14:35.360 --> 01:14:37.000
After them!

1050
01:14:39.600 --> 01:14:41.680
(GROANS. SCREAMS)

1051
01:14:44.040 --> 01:14:47.000
(BARKING. GROWLING)
Whoa! Hey!

1052
01:14:47.080 --> 01:14:48.600
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1053
01:14:51.200 --> 01:14:52.520
MAN: They're getting away!

1054
01:15:01.920 --> 01:15:04.160
Follow me. Rool.
I don't know.
Where are you?

1055
01:15:04.240 --> 01:15:06.640
(GRUNTING)

1056
01:15:06.720 --> 01:15:08.640
Oh. no. where did
everybody go?

1057
01:15:08.720 --> 01:15:10.360
Maybe it was
something we said.

1058
01:15:16.680 --> 01:15:18.360
(MADMARTIGAN SCREAMS)

1059
01:15:27.080 --> 01:15:29.680
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1060
01:15:36.640 --> 01:15:37.960
(MOANING)

1061
01:15:38.120 --> 01:15:40.080
(MOANING. GROANING)

1062
01:15:40.200 --> 01:15:42.880
(LAUGHING)

1063
01:15:48.080 --> 01:15:50.320
(SCREAMS)

1064
01:16:04.560 --> 01:16:06.560
(SCREAMS)

1065
01:16:10.920 --> 01:16:13.240
(SCREAMING)

1066
01:16:16.960 --> 01:16:18.480
(CLATTERING)

1067
01:16:18.640 --> 01:16:20.440
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

1068
01:16:21.120 --> 01:16:22.320
(ELORA GIGGLING)

1069
01:16:29.880 --> 01:16:30.920
Madmartigan!

1070
01:16:44.720 --> 01:16:46.080
(COW MOOS)

1071
01:16:48.200 --> 01:16:49.520
Madmartigan!

1072
01:16:50.480 --> 01:16:51.840
What the hell
happened up there?

1073
01:16:52.360 --> 01:16:54.440
You started spouting poetry.

1074
01:16:54.800 --> 01:16:56.840
Poetry?
Yeah.

1075
01:16:57.160 --> 01:17:00.320
"I love you. Sorsha.
I worship you. Sorsha."

1076
01:17:00.640 --> 01:17:02.080
You almost got us killed!

1077
01:17:02.920 --> 01:17:04.200
"I love you. Sorsha"?

1078
01:17:04.640 --> 01:17:06.480
I don't love her.
She kicked me in the face.

1079
01:17:07.120 --> 01:17:09.520
I hate her! Don't I?

1080
01:17:10.680 --> 01:17:12.120
(CAWING)

1081
01:17:12.680 --> 01:17:14.560
Kael! Kael!

1082
01:17:15.400 --> 01:17:16.800
Nockmaar soldiers!

1083
01:17:20.000 --> 01:17:22.520
MAN: Hide!
Get the children!
Come on!

1084
01:17:25.360 --> 01:17:26.440
Go on. hide! Get the children!

1085
01:17:26.520 --> 01:17:27.840
They're after us!
We need a place to hide.

1086
01:17:27.920 --> 01:17:31.120
Come on. Follow me.
Quick! Come on! Move!

1087
01:17:47.880 --> 01:17:49.360
I knew you'd get
out of that rat trap.

1088
01:17:53.040 --> 01:17:54.560
You left me to die. Airk.

1089
01:17:54.840 --> 01:17:56.720
I probably saved your life.

1090
01:17:57.200 --> 01:17:58.640
We were slaughtered.
and I lost a lot...

1091
01:17:58.720 --> 01:18:00.040
Shh! Quiet!
(HORSE WHINNYING)

1092
01:18:02.160 --> 01:18:03.560
KAEL: Tear this village apart!

1093
01:18:04.400 --> 01:18:05.720
Look everywhere!

1094
01:18:06.960 --> 01:18:08.280
Find the child!

1095
01:18:13.920 --> 01:18:15.040
(CRYING)

1096
01:18:17.880 --> 01:18:20.520
(CAWING. IMITATING BABY)
(SHUSHING)

1097
01:18:26.280 --> 01:18:28.240
(SHUSHING)

1098
01:18:29.280 --> 01:18:31.440
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY)

1099
01:18:44.080 --> 01:18:46.440
KAEL: Tell Sorsha
I search the north bank!

1100
01:18:46.760 --> 01:18:48.080
(KAEL GRUNTS)
SOLDIER: Yes. General.

1101
01:19:02.280 --> 01:19:04.200
Quiet. (SHUSHING)
(FUSSING)

1102
01:19:21.280 --> 01:19:23.440
(SORSHA SCREAMS. GRUNTS)

1103
01:19:23.520 --> 01:19:26.480
Sorsha!
Back.

1104
01:19:27.800 --> 01:19:29.160
Back!

1105
01:19:35.160 --> 01:19:36.480
Back!

1106
01:19:38.400 --> 01:19:40.800
Keep the baby quiet.
She needs to be changed.

1107
01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:43.840
Nockmaar scum!
You'll never defeat us.

1108
01:19:44.280 --> 01:19:45.840
Give up the baby!
Shut up!

1109
01:19:47.800 --> 01:19:49.320
What does Bavmorda want
with this baby. anyway?

1110
01:19:50.120 --> 01:19:51.160
WILLOW: She's a princess.

1111
01:19:51.280 --> 01:19:53.520
We're taking her
to Tir Asleen.
Tir Asleen?

1112
01:19:54.240 --> 01:19:56.720
Even if you could find it.
peck. she's right.

1113
01:19:57.000 --> 01:19:58.480
You'd never get past
the Nockmaar army.

1114
01:19:59.160 --> 01:20:01.080
There's an even bigger army
at Tir Asleen.

1115
01:20:01.160 --> 01:20:03.680
If we can just get there...
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

1116
01:20:07.640 --> 01:20:09.640
I've lost
more than half my men
fighting Bavmorda.

1117
01:20:10.320 --> 01:20:11.720
Now you and this peck
are gonna take her on?

1118
01:20:13.200 --> 01:20:15.120
You always told me
you served no one.
Madmartigan.

1119
01:20:15.880 --> 01:20:17.280
Since when are you
a crusader?

1120
01:20:20.120 --> 01:20:21.520
He's not
gonna help you. peck.

1121
01:20:23.440 --> 01:20:24.880
He's a worthless thief.

1122
01:20:26.920 --> 01:20:28.280
I'm not a thief. Airk.

1123
01:20:29.520 --> 01:20:30.880
He's not a thief.

1124
01:20:33.920 --> 01:20:35.280
Are you?

1125
01:20:49.560 --> 01:20:50.880
I serve the Nelwyn. Airk.

1126
01:20:57.760 --> 01:21:00.240
Want to come with us?
You'll never make it.
Madmartigan.

1127
01:21:02.680 --> 01:21:04.080
Then once again
we say goodbye.

1128
01:21:07.560 --> 01:21:09.400
(CLAMORING)
(GROANING)

1129
01:21:18.360 --> 01:21:19.720
Over here!

1130
01:21:19.800 --> 01:21:21.160
Sorsha!

1131
01:21:21.760 --> 01:21:23.080
Weapons down or she's dead!

1132
01:21:30.520 --> 01:21:31.760
Hyah! Hyah!

1133
01:21:38.400 --> 01:21:40.200
LIEUTENANT:
Get to your horses!
After 'em!

1134
01:21:42.640 --> 01:21:43.960
(SCREAMING)

1135
01:21:57.080 --> 01:21:58.280
(CAWING)

1136
01:22:26.640 --> 01:22:27.840
RAZIEL: This way!

1137
01:22:27.960 --> 01:22:29.000
This way!

1138
01:22:29.120 --> 01:22:31.840
As the crow flies. you fools!

1139
01:22:38.600 --> 01:22:40.160
You're holding me too tight!

1140
01:22:40.600 --> 01:22:41.600
I don't want you to get away.

1141
01:22:41.680 --> 01:22:45.960
Why? Because I'm "your sun.
your moon. your starlit sky"?

1142
01:22:48.120 --> 01:22:50.120
Get your hair out of my face.
or I'll chop it off.

1143
01:22:54.240 --> 01:22:55.600
Did I really...

1144
01:22:56.040 --> 01:22:58.080
Did I really say
those things last night?

1145
01:22:58.200 --> 01:22:59.520
In your tent?

1146
01:22:59.600 --> 01:23:00.880
You said you loved me.

1147
01:23:01.520 --> 01:23:03.360
I don't remember that.
You lied to me!

1148
01:23:04.040 --> 01:23:05.360
No. I...

1149
01:23:06.520 --> 01:23:08.200
I just wasn't myself
last night.

1150
01:23:09.200 --> 01:23:12.720
I suppose my power
enchanted you. and you were
helpless against it.

1151
01:23:14.200 --> 01:23:15.680
Sort of.
Then what?

1152
01:23:17.360 --> 01:23:18.680
It went away.

1153
01:23:19.200 --> 01:23:20.560
It went away?

1154
01:23:20.720 --> 01:23:22.360
"I dwell in darkness
without you."

1155
01:23:22.480 --> 01:23:24.160
and it went away?
Yeah.

1156
01:23:24.240 --> 01:23:25.480
(GRUNTS)

1157
01:23:28.680 --> 01:23:29.880
(MADMARTIGAN ROARS)

1158
01:23:31.360 --> 01:23:33.360
(SHOUTS)
(GRUNTS)

1159
01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:38.080
Whoa.
(SORSHA PANTING)

1160
01:23:47.360 --> 01:23:48.880
RAZIEL: Hurry! Kael's coming!

1161
01:23:48.960 --> 01:23:50.240
(SQUAWKS)

1162
01:23:50.360 --> 01:23:52.120
(GRUNTING. GROANING)

1163
01:23:53.640 --> 01:23:55.680
Madmartigan. come on! Now!

1164
01:23:57.080 --> 01:23:58.560
(GROANING)

1165
01:24:01.760 --> 01:24:02.760
(COUGHS)

1166
01:24:03.920 --> 01:24:05.720
Madmartigan. come on!

1167
01:24:07.560 --> 01:24:09.440
RAZIEL: They're coming! Away!

1168
01:24:10.320 --> 01:24:11.680
WILLOW: Go on! Hyah!

1169
01:24:26.600 --> 01:24:27.680
(YELLS)

1170
01:24:30.120 --> 01:24:31.320
KAEL: Whoa! Whoa!

1171
01:24:32.800 --> 01:24:34.280
This way!
This way!

1172
01:24:34.400 --> 01:24:35.400
(ALL URGING HORSES)

1173
01:24:40.440 --> 01:24:44.240
RAZIEL: Tir Asleen!
At last. Tir Asleen!

1174
01:24:55.280 --> 01:24:56.560
MADMARTIGAN: Hello?

1175
01:24:56.640 --> 01:24:58.080
(WIND WHISTLING)

1176
01:24:58.600 --> 01:24:59.920
Hello?

1177
01:25:04.280 --> 01:25:05.600
Hello?

1178
01:25:07.800 --> 01:25:09.480
Why did I listen to you. peck?

1179
01:25:10.320 --> 01:25:13.160
"Everything will be all right
once we get to Tir Asleen."

1180
01:25:14.720 --> 01:25:15.920
The only army around here

1181
01:25:16.000 --> 01:25:19.160
is the one that's about
to ride across this valley
and wipe us out!

1182
01:25:19.920 --> 01:25:22.320
But Cherlindrea said
we'd be safe here.

1183
01:25:23.320 --> 01:25:26.000
"Safe"? Look at these people.

1184
01:25:26.560 --> 01:25:28.080
This place is cursed. peck.

1185
01:25:28.560 --> 01:25:30.680
It's falling apart.
Open your eyes!

1186
01:25:30.800 --> 01:25:32.120
And it...
(ELORA COOS)

1187
01:25:34.840 --> 01:25:36.160
Trolls.

1188
01:25:39.400 --> 01:25:40.800
I hate trolls.

1189
01:25:41.760 --> 01:25:44.240
RAZIEL: This is the work
of Bavmorda.

1190
01:25:44.560 --> 01:25:45.840
(ELORA GRUNTS)

1191
01:25:53.640 --> 01:25:55.000
RAZIEL: Willow?

1192
01:25:55.200 --> 01:25:56.200
The wand.

1193
01:25:56.320 --> 01:25:58.480
Turn me back
into my human form.

1194
01:25:58.560 --> 01:25:59.960
Are you sure?

1195
01:26:12.560 --> 01:26:13.880
(LAUGHS)

1196
01:26:15.800 --> 01:26:17.120
Yeah.

1197
01:26:18.240 --> 01:26:19.560
Good.

1198
01:26:26.720 --> 01:26:28.880
RAZIEL: Hurry. Willow.
Transform me.

1199
01:26:29.040 --> 01:26:31.720
I can't do it.
I'm just not a sorcerer.

1200
01:26:31.840 --> 01:26:33.240
But you can be.

1201
01:26:33.360 --> 01:26:37.440
Speak. and be one
with the words.

1202
01:26:37.920 --> 01:26:39.560
(CHANTING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

1203
01:26:41.200 --> 01:26:42.560
(CAWING)

1204
01:26:44.720 --> 01:26:46.920
RAZIEL: Oh. Willow.
you're losing me.

1205
01:26:47.040 --> 01:26:48.280
(HORSES WHINNY)

1206
01:26:48.760 --> 01:26:50.080
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1207
01:26:51.600 --> 01:26:53.840
Madmartigan. Kael's coming!

1208
01:26:53.920 --> 01:26:56.920
RAZIEL: Willow. you idiot.

1209
01:26:57.280 --> 01:26:58.640
Raziel?

1210
01:26:58.880 --> 01:27:01.080
Willow. arm that catapult
up there.

1211
01:27:04.280 --> 01:27:05.560
(GRUNTING)

1212
01:27:12.640 --> 01:27:13.920
(GRUNTING)

1213
01:27:21.200 --> 01:27:23.240
(LAUGHING)
ALL: Whoa! Whoa!

1214
01:27:23.800 --> 01:27:26.920
RAZIEL: Good work.
Madmartigan.

1215
01:27:27.600 --> 01:27:28.920
What the hell happened to you?

1216
01:27:29.240 --> 01:27:31.280
KAEL: Assault!
Sorsha. battering ram!

1217
01:27:37.240 --> 01:27:38.600
SORSHA: Cut it down!

1218
01:27:50.400 --> 01:27:51.680
Faster!

1219
01:28:06.320 --> 01:28:07.680
KAEL: Forward!

1220
01:28:08.120 --> 01:28:09.800
Break it down!

1221
01:28:25.200 --> 01:28:26.320
(GROWLS)

1222
01:28:29.960 --> 01:28:32.200
KAEL: Again! Again!

1223
01:28:35.280 --> 01:28:36.720
(GROWLING)

1224
01:28:37.040 --> 01:28:39.320
RAZIEL: Willow.
use the wand on that troll.

1225
01:28:39.840 --> 01:28:41.000
(GROWLING)

1226
01:28:42.040 --> 01:28:43.200
(SPEAKS OTHER LANGUAGE)

1227
01:28:43.280 --> 01:28:44.640
(SCREAMING)

1228
01:28:55.280 --> 01:28:57.440
(GROWLING)
Ew!

1229
01:28:57.560 --> 01:28:58.560
(GRUNTS)

1230
01:29:06.400 --> 01:29:09.400
KAEL: Break it down! Forward!

1231
01:29:11.240 --> 01:29:13.600
(SHOUTING)
(YELLS)

1232
01:29:21.400 --> 01:29:23.880
(YELLING)

1233
01:29:25.760 --> 01:29:27.160
ALL: Whoa! Whoa!

1234
01:29:27.240 --> 01:29:28.720
(HORSE WHINNIES)

1235
01:29:37.320 --> 01:29:38.600
(GASPS)

1236
01:29:39.760 --> 01:29:41.760
(ROARING)

1237
01:29:56.960 --> 01:29:58.400
KAEL: Get him!

1238
01:29:58.560 --> 01:30:00.200
(ALL SHOUTING)

1239
01:30:02.240 --> 01:30:03.720
(ROARING)

1240
01:30:18.160 --> 01:30:19.440
(WILLOW YELLS)

1241
01:30:21.120 --> 01:30:22.480
The other side!

1242
01:30:26.240 --> 01:30:27.480
(SCREAMING)

1243
01:30:37.160 --> 01:30:39.760
KAEL: Destroy the beast!
Find the baby!

1244
01:30:40.000 --> 01:30:42.320
RAZIEL: (BLEATS) Take that!

1245
01:30:42.640 --> 01:30:43.640
(GROWLING)

1246
01:30:45.440 --> 01:30:47.400
(GROWLING)
(CRYING)

1247
01:30:49.000 --> 01:30:51.480
(GROWLING)
(SCREAMING)

1248
01:31:08.640 --> 01:31:09.640
WILLOW: Oh!

1249
01:31:11.200 --> 01:31:13.000
